                            <comment id="14428710" author="jglick" created="Tue, 5 Apr 2011 09:48:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for PLXCOMP-87 seems to have broken parsing of the Windows drive letter. Unit test coverage for this rather subtle parsing code is quite poor.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14428645" author="jglick" created="Tue, 5 Apr 2011 10:14:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch incl. unit test which seems to fix the issue. Confirmed by building patched version of &lt;tt&gt;plexus-compiler-javac&lt;/tt&gt;, including that as a dep in &lt;tt&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/tt&gt;, and requesting the patched plugin in a Maven project on which &lt;a href=&quot;http://netbeans.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=197381&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://netbeans.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=197381&lt;/a&gt; could previously be reproduced.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14428699" author="krosenvold" created="Thu, 23 Feb 2012 15:37:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in 32ef15b5a277015a4071486c3a00db6853fab2d4, thanks for the patch !&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
